snippet.textDisplay:
Here is my take - The theme is quite simple. Espionage / Doomsday film. They somehow figure out a way to travel bit ahead in time.. maybe few seconds (10sec-tenet!) and come back in reverse, literally.. against arrow of time; trying to catch / anticipate the exact moment of threat and stop it. Things happen in real time and with arrow of time but from protagonist perspective it happens in reverse.. car accident, bullets on windows, ship in reverse scenes. Nolan will definitely mix it up and show frames from either perspectives and viewers need to figure out who’s perspective they are watching at any given moment. Hence the palindrome name too.. TENET! 😉
It’s a beautiful take on arrow of time linked with second law of thermodynamics. So the visuals and VFX will be mind blowing and confusing and hence the high budget production. Memento skipped to frames in reverse chronology and then showed them forward but tenet will show the frames in reverse literally intermingled with natural flow. Very neat and smart!

snippet.textDisplay: We saw the trailer at the new Star Wars. It was about 15 mins long. It was so long and un-trailer like as it had no intro or info, and seemed more like a short film. People started to wonder if we were in the wrong screen!? Of course i'll watch this film when it comes out, but the trailer was odd. A gang of masked men busting into an orchestra performance, assaulting musicians and destroying some guys cello. Assaulting audience members and then blowing up all those innocent people. With no apparent reasoning and a lot of over kill!.. I didnt like the trailer at the cinema. Like i said, Its a Nolan movie so i will be watching all the same.
